    "oceandeep",
    "bright",
    "aether",
    "guru-bin",
    "collaboration",
    "stratum"
  ],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OPENSKY — Above the Cloud Line",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "Discovery 6: HP Filter Coupling — sky_filterHP=200 leaves room for OCEANDEEP below (Full Column Principle)",
      "Canon 2: The Flying Fish Does Not Compete With the Anglerfish — they share the column",
      "Verse 6: Full Column Architecture — two engines spanning trench to stratosphere as one instrument"
    ],
    "revelation": "The Full Column Principle: HP at 200 Hz means OPENSKY starts exactly where OCEANDEEP ends. Zero overlap. Two engines, one instrument. The water column made musical.",
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "Load this preset and OCEANDEEP's Full Column Low simultaneously. Play both. The water column — from the midnight zone to the stratosphere — exists as one continuous sound. The Guru says: the Aquarium is not a metaphor. It is a mixing console. OPENSKY is the surface light. OCEANDEEP is the pressure. Together they are the ocean and the sky and all the space between.",
    "diagnosis": "Full Column High is architecturally paired with OCEANDEEP Full Column Low. FilterHP=200 is the handoff frequency. No sub (subLevel=0.0) to avoid masking the bass register OCEANDEEP owns. ShimmerFeedback=0.55 (hall zone) keeps the sky layer spacious and non-competitive. StereoWidth=0.88 occupies the full stereo image from 200 Hz upward."
  },
